gcc-config 2.0

gcc-config 2.0 is incompatible with previous versions of gcc-config.  A
migration path has not been implemented yet.

configuration directory: /etc/gcc-config
All configuration information is stored in this directory.  The current config
format is as follows, but this should change before release to allow for an
easy upgrade path.  XML would be nice, but I believe that would be too strong
a dependency for this package, but if someone wants to implement that, I would
be happy with it.  This code should be abstract enough that it can be used for
binutils (specifically ld and as) as well.

The selection file (/etc/gcc-config/selection.conf) lists the currently selected
profiles for each CHOST handled by gcc-config.  It is formatted as follows:
<CHOST> <CONFIGURATION FILE (without leading /etc/gcc-config/)> <PROFILE NAME>

Configuration file (for each installed gcc package) is formatted as follows:
<PROFILE NAME>
<default CHOST for this profile>
<gcc specs file>
<LDPATH>
<additional CFLAGS to prepend to the command line>

Example /etc/gcc-config/master.conf:
x86_64-pc-linux-gnu x86_64-pc-linux-gnu-3.4.4.conf amd64-vanilla
i686-pc-linux-gnu x86_64-pc-linux-gnu-3.4.4.conf x86-vanilla
pentium4-pc-linux-gnu x86_64-pc-linux-gnu-3.4.4.conf p4-vanilla

Example /etc/gcc-config/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu-3.4.4.conf:
amd64-vanilla
x86_64-pc-linux-gnu
/usr/lib/gcc/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu/3.4.4/vanilla.specs
/usr/lib/gcc/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu/3.4.4/
-m64
amd64-hardened
x86_64-pc-linux-gnu
/usr/lib/gcc/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu/3.4.4/hardened.specs
/usr/lib/gcc/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu/3.4.4/
-m64
x86-vanilla
i686-pc-linux-gnu
/usr/lib/gcc/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu/3.4.4/vanilla.specs
/usr/lib/gcc/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu/3.4.4/32/
-m32
p4-vanilla
pentium4-pc-linux-gnu
/usr/lib/gcc/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu/3.4.4/vanilla.specs
/usr/lib/gcc/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu/3.4.4/32/
-m32 -march=pentium4
